text: DZEC-TV, channel 25 (analog) and channel 28 (digital) is the flagship UHF television station of Philippine television network Net 25, owned by Eagle Broadcasting Corporation. ==Digital channels== DZEC-TV broadcasts its digital signal on UHF Channel 28 (557.143MHz) and is multiplexed into the following subchannels: Channel Video Aspect Short name Programming Note 25.1 1080i 16:9 NET25 HD Net 25 (Main DZEC-TV programming)/Eagle Broadcasting Corporation Test broadcast 25.2 480i 16:9 NET25 SD Net 25 (Main DZEC-TV programming)/Eagle Broadcasting Corporation Test broadcast 25.3 1080i 16:9 INCTV HD INC TV (Main DZCE-TV programming) Test broadcast 25.4 480i 16:9 INCTV SD INC TV (Main DZCE- TV programming) Test broadcast 25.5 480i 16:9 EBC RESERVED Net 25 Test broadcast In addition, Eagle Broadcasting Corporation operates its channel on DZCE-TV UHF Channel 49 (683.143MHz) Channel Video Aspect Short name Programming Note 01.1 1080i 16:9 INCTV HD INC TV (Main DZCE-TV programming) Test broadcast 01.2 1080i 16:9 NET25 HD Net 25 (Main DZEC-TV programming) Test broadcast 01.3 480i 16:9 INCTV SD INC TV Test broadcast == Areas of Coverage == === Primary areas === * Metro Manila * Cavite * Bulacan * Laguna * Rizal === Secondary areas === * Portion of Pampanga * Portion of Nueva Ecija * Portion of Tarlac * Portion of Zambales * Portion of Bataan * Portion of Batangas * Portion of Quezon ==Related pages== *Eagle Broadcasting Corporation *Net 25 *Eagle FM 95.5 *INC TV *DZEC Radyo Agila 1062 ==References== ==Other websites== *Net-25 Official Website Category:1999 establishments in Asia Category:Filipino television stations
